{
    "name": "Monitor Lizard",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> warm forests or plains<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, or pack (3\u20138)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Poison (Ex)</b> Bite\u2014injury; <i>save </i>Fort DC 14; <i>onset </i>1 minute; <i>frequency </i>1/hour for 6 hours; <i>effect </i>1d2 Dexterity damage; <i>cure </i>1 save. The save DC is Constitution-based."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Monitor lizards are large enough to pose a threat to humans, and in some societies are often mistaken for dragons. Some can reach lengths of 10 feet or more and weights of 350 pounds."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This immense lizard moves with a slow but relentless gait. Its feet end in large talons, and ropes of drool hang from its toothy maw.</i>",
